<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 11:39AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Le
Flore County through 1215 PM CDT...
At 1139 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
southeast of Heavener, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Heavener...                       Hodgen...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
